title: Updated List Of Applications and Department Partners Using Login.Gov For Identity Management

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

An updated list of applications and department partners currently using login.gov for identity management as described by https://login.gov/partners/, as well as applications and partners that intend to use login.gov but are not yet currently actively using the service.

"Login.gov has over 30 agency partners. Our product is integrated with over 300 live applications and services including 12 Cabinet level agencies such as the Department of Defense, Department of Homeland Security, and the Department of Energy."

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Tod Elario

title: UT Austin Arrest of Photojournalist, April 24, 2025 (Austin Police Department)

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Texas Public Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

1. Any recording (including audio or video captured by body camera, vehicular camera, or handheld device) of the detention of Carlos, a photojournalist employed by FOX 7, on April 24, 2024, at or near UT Austin. For any recording of the detention, please include any audio or video captured five minutes before his detention and twenty minutes after the recording captured any audio or video of his detention.

2. Any report concerning the arrest or interaction with Carlos on April 24, 2024.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Adam Steinbaugh
